  { q: 'Will a Thunderbolt 4 dock work with M1 and M2 MacBooks?', a: 'Yes. Thunderbolt 4 docks are backward compatible with Thunderbolt 3 ports on Intel Macs and the Thunderbolt/USB-4 ports on Apple Silicon Macs. Just note that M1 Macs support only one external display — M2 Pro, M3, and M-series Pro/Max chips unlock dual display.' },
